In c++ we have inbuilt function for gcd.

FUNCTION is
int a,b;
gcd_val = gcd(a,b);

It is done using the euclidean algorithm

EUCLIDEAN ALGO - gcd(a,b) = gcd(a-b,b) where a>b;
for code can be written as gcd(a,b) = gcd(a%b,b) where a>b;

int findGcd(int a, int b) {
    while(a > 0 && b > 0) {
        if(a > b) {
            a = a % b;
        }
        else {
            b = b % a; 
        }
    }
    if(a == 0) {
        return b;
    }
    return a;
}
